name: places/ChIJf7oVJ3oR2jERYufsyQQd-3k/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURJNjRTdUV3EAE
text:
{'text': 'Ordered cafe latte  w oat milk (5.50 +1 for the oat milk), earl grey pot (8.50) and a waffle w double scoop (10.30).

Waffle nice, nothing to crow about but kinda small for the price.

Quite sure they use some cheap loose leaf tea which has only a v faint Earl grey taste, if u even can call it that... really not worth the price.

Coffee is the only saving grace, quite robust n smooth.

Service is not bad. The lady was quick to note that we have kids at the table and changed some of the utensils to kids bowl n utensils without us asking.

Kids were asking for fries, but the 13.50 for garlic truffle fries is really kinda expensive so we decide to spare our wallet the trauma.

Atmosphere is nice. Will be a good place to come chill on a lazy afternoon, if u can afford the food.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJf7oVJ3oR2jERYufsyQQd-3k/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNZNXZySkt3EAE
text:
{'text': 'If David Copperfield retired from showbiz and opened a café, Cuppafield would be his masterpiece. The cosy brick walls, warm lighting, and slightly mysterious vibe made me feel like I’d stepped into a magician’s study—only instead of pulling rabbits from hats, they pull steaks from dreams.

I ordered the steak with mashed potatoes, a sunny-side-up egg, and a side of gravy that deserves its own Netflix special. The steak was perfectly cooked, the potatoes were smoother than a card trick, and the tea? Black, bold, and brewed by a wizard. Bonus points for letting me enjoy it all next to my Kindle—nothing like literature and meat to make a night magical.

I highly recommend this enchanting little place to anyone craving great food and warm tea and possibly a disappearing act for their problems. Cuppafield, you’ve earned your wand.

#CuppafieldMagic #TeaAndIllusions #SteakOfWonder', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJf7oVJ3oR2jERYufsyQQd-3k/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURYNHRxcE5REAE
text: {'text': 'The restaurant gives a peaceful and pleasant ambience, and the service was good. The fish and chips were hot and delicious, but the buffalo wings, while crispy, could benefit from a more flavorful sauce. The spaghetti, while flavorful with a nice garlic taste, had noodles that were a bit too firm.  The waffle with milo ice cream was enjoyable, but I found the $5.50 waffle and $6+ ice cream to be a bit overpriced.\n\nOverall, the experience was pleasant, but the portions were on the smaller side, which might be a concern for those with larger appetites.  The prices were slightly higher than I expected for a neighborhood cafe, but the lack of GST and service charge helps to offset that.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJf7oVJ3oR2jERYufsyQQd-3k/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNnb3VyZUVBEAE
text: {'text': 'Atmosphere was nice. Nice music. However, the light a little dim especially when it’s cloudy outside. Have to squint my eyes to read the menu.\n\nThe garlic truffle fries is a must order. Had the cheese baked rice and mushroom aglio olio. The rice was ok. A little wet but still eatable. For the aglio olio. Can skip. The mocha was nicely done.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJf7oVJ3oR2jERYufsyQQd-3k/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURiNG9UTTdnRRAB
text: {'text': 'Overall, nice cafe to hang around in the neighbourhood. Really enjoyed the mashed potato with brown gravy from that grilled chicken. Really nice fries with seasoning and decent beef patty. The garlic flavour was really brought across from the pasta. Mac and cheese a little too sweet but maybe kids might like , idk … the waffle is really worth trying. Ice cream is average. Lovely staffs and seats are quite comfortable.', 'languageCode': 'en'}
